    "We use GPT-4o-mini model to emulate a user persona with a hidden preference ℎ and allow it to respond with sentiment-driven feedback.",
    "More details about the simulation in Appendix G. This experiment is further validated through the real world user study in Section 5.",
    "Computational Experiments Results(E1) Effect of Steering on Content and Quality.",
    "We apply steering for all models and preference dimensions with strength factors between -30 < 𝑑 < 30, measuring the mean preference effect across the LLM's responses to the OASST2 query dataset.Figure 2 shows the standard (top) and perplexity-normalized (bottom) preference effects for all models and preferences.",
    "The values are standardized to center around 𝑑 = 0 as the neutral point with effect=0.Under ideal circumstances, we expect to see a linear increase in preference expression corresponding to the increasing steering strength."
